6:
Gah! This is just so typical of you,
breaking promises like this!
10:
When are you going to get your act
together and stop being such a DITZ,
little miss Drum Major?
12:
We were supposed to have a
meeting to discuss the schedule for
using the field! Let me guess, you
forgot?
16:
I did. I'm really sorry... It just
completely slipped my mind!
20:
B-but, you managed to take care of
it on your own, Elsie! And while you
were off doing that, I got in some
practice with the others!
26:
Don't think that crappy excuse is
gonna work on me!
30:
Oh, looks like someone's calling me!
Sorry Elsie, gotta run!
34:
I'm getting a weird sense of déjà vu
here. Not much has changed in the
Marching Band club, it seems.
38: Those two are really good friends.
42:
It's you adventurers again... Where
are you whisking Marchella off to
this time?!
47:
Is our reputation really that bad...?
We're not doing anything of the
sort—we're just passing by!
57:
Please don't use that boring
nickname with me! My goodness,
Marchella's already tainted you...
61:
My name is Eloise Magento. I'm the
only daughter—and heir—of the
Magento family, who run Palpebra's
BIGGEST business.
64:
I'll forgive you this time, because
you're friends of Marchella... But
know that you should mind your
words with me, adventurers!
67:
Oh come on. You always said you
liked the nickname Marchella gave
you.
71:
You there! Did you just say
something? For your sake, I certainly
hope you didn't.
74:
Oh, whatever. There was, in fact,
something I wanted to talk to you
about. Do you have a moment,
Stella, Alk?
78:
Wow, you remembered our names.
Didn't expect that.
83:
Of course. I didn't use your names
earlier because I was angry. Rest
assured, I've done my research on
you.
86:
You've got political connections in
the upper echelons of the Guild AND
the Farlands. But that's not all...
88:
The serpent attack during the 50th
anniversary celebrations, the
Halloween affair, the Valentine's
fiasco...
90:
Your group is at the center of every
conflict resolution in the city. And
you have a base—"Starview Village,"
was it?
94:
...Huh. You weren't kidding. You really
did do your research.
98:
Hohoho! I hope I haven't scared you
off with just that. I'm one of
Palpebra's financial elites—I'm
capable of much more!
102:
Though I admit, judging from your
résumés, you're nothing to sneeze at
either.
105:
And what's more, our Drum Major
seems to place a lot of trust in you.
109:
Boy, you're really her number one
fan, aren't you?
114:
E-excuse me? I am NOT!
Are you trying to provoke me?
123:
There you are, Eloise! According to
school regulation #17, I hereby
challenge you to a duel... The prize
will be the right to use the school
field!
126:
Regulation #17... "Exceptional
provisions for conflict resolution via
magic duel." You failed at
discussion, so now you turn to
violence?
129:
Fine. I accept your citation of our
antiquated school rules. You know
this means we'll be audited by the
Morality Committee.
132:
So what? Are you scared? Figures. A
bunch of nobodies who spend all
day tooting on horns would never
stand a chance against us!
139:
Run your mouth all you want. You
know it's WE who take our studies
more seriously and who contribute
more to this school.
150:
Let me speak nice and slow so even
you dung-for-brains meatheads will
understand.
153:
Do you. 
Have any idea. 
Who you're messing with?
157:
I'm a member of House Magento!
We don't settle for anything less
than the TOP. From where I stand,
you miserable goons are like ants.
160:
So make sure I never see your ugly
mugs again! 
Hehe... Hohoho!
163:
My sincerest apologies for the
disturbance back there.
167:
No, it's all right. That was... actually
kind of badass.
171:
Heh. But of course. I am a Magento,
after all.
174:
We always aim for the top, no
matter what. Frankly, it's a matter of
pride for me.
178:
Say. Would you be willing to strike
up a deal with me?
181:
Ever since she became friends with
you, Marchella's gotten stronger.
More tenacious. I can't let her
upstage me!
185:
Which is why I want you to let me
join your ranks. I'm sure I've already
proven that I'm more than capable
of keeping up.
188:
You get to make an ally of House
Magento, and I get to learn the
secrets of Marchella's sudden
growth. Win-win!
198:
I mean, deal aside, you're a friend of
our friend, right? Can't go wrong. I'm
sure Marchella will be happy to hear
this.
204:
A friend of friend... is also a friend. Is
that so...
210: You cut that crap RIGHT NOW!
213:
I'll take a HARD pass on being added
to your team just out of pity! I'm
worth something on my own
merits—and I plan to show you!
219:
First of all, let the record state that
Marchella and I are RIVALS! We are
not, as you suggested, something
as naive as mere "friends."
228:
Well then! It's time to head off. Take
me with you, and facilitate my
growth. Level me up as soon as
possible!
231:
You should consider yourselves
lucky! A big shot like me, on your
side?! Haha! Ohohoho!
